<br>
Is it when I get too close and I get stunned and then whacked for multiple hits to low health??<br>
<br>
No.<br>
<br>
Is it when I snare four and find I have two more in that group I didn't know I had?<br>
<br>
No.<br>
<br>
Is it when I snare three and the fourth takes two additional snares and I have to re-round and resnare?<br>
<br>
No.<br>
<br>
Is it when I'm totally OOM and I have four unsnared critters at below half health running me down?<br>
<br>
No.<br>
<br>
Is it when I'm in the situation above and I know my Tboots are about to expire?<br>
<br>
No.<br>
<br>
What terrifies me the most, you ask?<br>
<br>
Other players.<br>
<br>
Yes, when I'm doing a multi-kite and I see another player running across my screen, that's when my heart just about leaps out of my chest.<br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Because they will probably do one of the following:<br>
<br>
1.  Steal one or more critters from my grouping.<br>
<br>
2.  Root one or more members from my grouping.<br>
<br>
3.  Bring along a mob that is not in my grouping to me so that it bashes me as an added agro.<br>
<br>
4.  Distract me in some way that I get too close to my grouping and get thwacked but good.<br>
<br>
5.  Cause my already snared grouping to ungroup while I'm snaring the one resist and attempting to regroup.<br>
<br>
Yes.  All of the above has happened to me in the past.  I've had druids pull one critter from my grouping.  I've had a guy root one in an attempt to &quot;help&quot; me.  I've come back from snaring the non-complaint and had all three of the others ungrouped.<br>
<br>
You all have similar experiences? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujerrek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jerrek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/10/01 7:26:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real Terror</span><hr size=1> I think the only &quot;terror&quot; I have is when I've got my 4 little whatevers all nicely tacked together and I'm plodding along like a good little wizard dropping AE's like they're going out of style..<br>
<br>
And then notice my spell isn't firing immediately when I hit the button..<br>
<br>
Then I notice the lag meter has gone from its normal 0% to, say, 28%.<br>
<br>
That's what scares me the most.  I usually run at full speed in the same direction until either the lag goes away fully, or I'm far enough to camp out.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utegellan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tegellan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/12/01 2:41:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real Terror</span><hr size=1>  aye, lag or another player is the most scary thing when quadding, lag is the worst though, all the times I have died while quadding raptors (except one) was due to lag =P<br>
<br>
 <p> <i>Tegellan Fey`Brandhe</i><BR>
 Evoker<Br>
 The Circle of Eternity<BR>
 <a href="mailto:tegellan@hotmail.com">tegellan@hotmail.com</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/12/01 12:11:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real Terror</span><hr size=1> Lag sucks, but you can't do anything about that ...<br>
<br>
<br>
Helpful players suck worse. I quad in CS all the time. If I see someone in the zone I don't know, I will wait to see what they are doing/where they are going. I avoid them like the plague.<br>
<br>
I think i have died to lag maybe 2-3 times, to other players a lot more. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Channeler of the 52nd Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
