</table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ustad6.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stad6</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 6:40:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real Terror</span><hr size=1> Other players siphoning off a mob happens semi-frequently, but that doesn't really scare me that much.  It just pisses me off; particularly since a lot of times it is a druid, who I feel should know better.<br>
<br>
The big one is the lag as the previous posts point out.  I had it happen in OT last night where my connection was seemingly coming to a halt only to restore at the last minute.  I found myself getting totally ripped and the mobs were no longer nicely grouped up.  Since the zone starts to green out at 45, I was able to round em up again and continue.  This is reason enough to use Steelskin or Diamondskin for every quad-kite.  It is truly a lifesaver.<br>
<br>
Only 3 deaths thus far from quadding, all of which were linkdeath deaths.<br>
<br>
