224 orbs of orange bubbliness<br>
Nameless<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 9:52:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real Terror</span><hr size=1> Just had a ranger root all four of my Ulthorks today, one at a time.  I have no idea what he was thinking.<br>
<br>
When I typed, &quot;Please don't mess up my quad.&quot;  he apologiezed profusely.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 1:10:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real Terror</span><hr size=1> Well, I must admin when you see someone running away from 4 angry mobs, it looks like they need help. Add a macro that uses say and something like I DON'T NEED HELP<br>
<br>
I have actually added a macro to that effect in GSAY for when I'm peeling off lowbie adds. <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Achieved Slayer<BR>
Assigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uishrafael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ishrafael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://members.home.net/biesiadam/pictures/smile.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 6:42:13 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/biesiadam/pictures/Ishyportrait1.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real Terror</span><hr size=1> I've found it helpful to do that... I just have a hotkey 'I'm pulling a quad, and just warning you in advance... I am doing this on purpose. Thanks.'<br>
<br>
aside from the many 'how do you quad?' questions, I don't have too many problems.  (I've had plenty of Ulthork swiped by suck ass druids... and I usually ask them if they want the whole lot of them... they usually stop)<br>
<br>
By the way, turned in 4 backpacks worth of ulthork tusks and got the following:<br>
1 blue diamond, 1 diamond, 2 black sapphires, ruby earring, ruby crown, a ruby, and a booby prize of crystallized sulpher.<br>
<br>
Keep your tusks.  Might not have the kind of luck I did, but you'll get some plat out of it, most likely.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now, the big question, where to go at 44... come on 51! (PoF and Atols!)<br>
 <p><img src=http://members.home.net/biesiadam/pictures/wizard.gif>  Ish</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 10:09:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real Terror</span><hr size=1> I think I'll make my CoF button have a &quot;I'm in a multi-kite, please do not attempt to assist me!&quot; or something.<br>
<br>
Level 44 is tough as is 45 and 46.  I still got decent XP at 44 at the Ulthork Warrior and Hunter camp.  At 45 I started dual-kiting Wooly Rhinos as well as quad-kiting Ulthorks.<br>
<br>
I've spent some time today at the Man-o-War camp South of Kael near NEG 8000 POS 3200.  If I quad walruses I'll spawn a man-o-war or two.  All man-o-wars are blue and can possibly drop the nice chest, neck, and legs. <br>
<br>
I did get lucky and got the SHM Tumultuous Strength spell which is fairly difficult for most SHM to get.  I gave a copy to a 56 luminary in my new guild.  I knew it might drop because I had gotten a copy already that I promised to another luminary.<br>
<br>
And, the man-o-wars do drop tusks too.  So far, I've not gotten anything terrific of late, but I have been lucky in the past.  Some of these walruses do give xp, but most don't.<br>
<br>
I experimented in the DL tonight.  Gnashers are a definite possibility *if* you snare first then round up.  I could not get distance on that sucker.  Forget ragers.  You can solo-kite them easily enough.<br>
<br>
If you can find and round up four Stonegazer Cockatrices I think you'd have the ultimate for the DL.  However, doing that and not agro'ing forty other critters might be difficult.<br>
<br>
Another place I need to try still is the plateau in EJ near the FoB zone line.<br>
